<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>get a goose egg • goose that lays the golden eggs</xh5><p> <i>get a goose egg—</i>1. <i>(Sport)</i> fail to score <i>(also: get a duck’s egg ):</i> Anytime you <u>get a goose egg</u> in modern-day football, it’s absolutely phenomenal. 2. <i>(sl.)</i> get a bump on the head: I walked into a door and <u>got a big goose egg</u> on my forehead. </p><p><i>goose that lays the golden eggs—</i>a source of wealth that should not be sacrificed <i>(in allusion to the proverb “kill the goose that lays the golden eggs”): </i>With recent developments in the airline industry, the last thing Atlanta needs is to lose faith in the <u>goose that lays the golden eggs</u>.</p> </entry>
